# SnoutSpotter Project Rules

## General
- Read `AGENTS.md` at the repo root for full project context before making changes.
- Region is `eu-west-1`. Never hardcode AWS account IDs — use CDK `Account` and `Region` tokens.
- All resources are tagged `Project: SnoutSpotter`.

## .NET / C#
- Target **.NET 8**. Use top-level statements in `Program.cs`.
- Use **record types** for API response models (see `src/api/Models/ClipModels.cs`).
- Register AWS SDK clients as singletons in DI.
- `AmazonIotDataClient` must use `ServiceURL` (not `RegionEndpoint`) — obtain via `iot:DescribeEndpoint`.
- After editing C# files, verify with: `dotnet build SnoutSpotter.sln`

## CDK Infrastructure
- Stacks live in `src/infra/Stacks/` and are wired in `src/infra/Program.cs`.
- Pass dependencies between stacks via typed `*Props` classes (e.g. `ApiStackProps`).
- ECR repos are created in **CoreStack** — never create them in consuming stacks.
- `IMAGE_TAG` env var controls Docker image tag at deploy time.
- Always deploy CoreStack before any stack that references its resources.

## Lambdas
- All Lambdas use **Docker-based deployment** via ECR.
- ASP.NET Core Lambdas use **Lambda Web Adapter** with `AWS_LWA_PORT=8080`.
- Each Lambda has its own `.csproj`, `Dockerfile`, and ECR repo.
- IoT control plane actions (e.g. `iot:DescribeEndpoint`) need `Resource: "*"` in IAM policies.

## Frontend (React)
- Stack: React 18 + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind CSS.
- Source is in `src/web/src/`. Pages in `pages/`, shared types in `types.ts`.
- API client is in `api.ts` — two base URLs: `VITE_API_URL` and `VITE_PI_MGMT_URL`.
- After editing frontend files, verify with: `npm run build` (from `src/web/`)
- DynamoDB Scan returns items in no guaranteed order — always sort client-side when needed.
- Use cursor-based pagination (`nextPageKey`), not offset-based (`page`/`pageSize`).

## Pi Software (Python)
- Scripts are in `src/pi/`. Config is in `config.yaml`.
- IoT thing names are prefixed `snoutspotter-` (e.g. `snoutspotter-garden`).
- `setup-pi.sh` handles full device provisioning — it calls the Pi Management API.
- Four systemd services: motion, uploader, health, ota.

## CI/CD
- GitHub Actions with OIDC AWS auth. Main pipeline is `deploy.yml`.
- Pipeline stages: infra → build images (parallel) → deploy stacks + web.
- Each component has its own build and deploy workflow in `.github/workflows/`.
- CloudFront must be invalidated after web deploys.

## Naming Conventions
- S3 bucket: `snout-spotter-{account-id}`
- DynamoDB table: `snout-spotter-clips`
- Lambda functions: `snout-spotter-api`, `snout-spotter-pi-mgmt`
- ECR repos: `snout-spotter-api`, `snout-spotter-ingest`, `snout-spotter-inference`, `snout-spotter-pi-mgmt`
- IoT Thing Group: `snoutspotter-pis`
- IoT Policy: `snoutspotter-pi-policy`
- IoT Things: `snoutspotter-{device-name}`
